Main epiproct sclerite (Ep-scl) : The main sclerite of the epiproct, sometimes called the upper limb of the epiproct (
Nelson & Baumann 1987
). It is open apically, usually divided in its dorsal portion, and can be divided or entire in its ventral and lateral portion; its ventral connection and lateral division are typical for the genera, as are the presence or absence of setae on its basocaudal portion ( Figs. 1–22 , Table 3 ).
